cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper is about temporal activity detection in videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture and loss function, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the form of activity labels and their super-classes, which could potentially fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, since the paper deals with videos, it could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
